{"id":"3177848_A_generalization_of_the_Levinson_algorithm_for_Hermitian_Toeplitz_matrices_with_any_rank_profile","abstract":"The paper describes a recursive algorithm for solving Hermitian Toeplitz systems of linear equations, without any restriction on the ranks of their nested Toeplitz subsystems. Such a general algorithm is needed, e.g., to obtain the eigenfilters for signal processing applications, or to compute the inverse of a nondefinite Toeplitz matrix. The regular portion of the algorithm is made of the classical Levinson recursion. The singular portion requires solving some well-defined systems of linear equations with gradient structure. The dimension of each of these sytems equals the amplitude of the corresponding singularity.","authors":["Philippe Delsarte","Y. Genin","YG KAMP"],"meta":["September 1985IEEE Transactions on Acoustics Speech and Signal Processing 33(4):964 - 971","DOI:10.1109/TASSP.1985.1164645","SourceIEEE Xplore"],"references":["266849956_Toeplitz_matrices","265435247_Geometry_of_polynomials_2nd_ed","265428522_Toeplitz_forms_and_their_applications_2nd_ed","250956308_On_Certain_Parallel_Toeplitz_Linear_System_Solvers","246535678_Inversion_of_Toeplitz_and_Hankel_matrices_with_singular_sections","243094196_Restrictions_of_Normal_Operators_Pade_Approximation_and_Autoregressive_Time_Series","242499304_The_Wiener_RMS_Root_Mean_Square_Error_Criterion_in_Filter_Design_and_Prediction","235146071_The_Laurent-Pade_Table","232952277_A_survey_of_Toeplitz_and_related_matrices","226092294_Parametric_toeplitz_systems","224738311_Linear_prediction_in_the_singular_case_and_the_stability_of_eigen_models","224680669_Inverses_of_Toeplitz_Operators_Innovations_and_Orthogonal_Polynomials","222441959_Fast_solution_of_Toeplitz_systems_and_computation_of_Pad_approximants","221678283_Linear_Prediction_A_Tutorial_Review","3999439_The_factorial_linear_modeling_A_Karhunen-Loeve_approach_to_speech_analysis","3186327_Pseudo-Lossless_Functions_with_Application_to_the_P